			<p>Hey Guy, <br />
a funny and insightful piece. <br />
However, I&#39;ve got some doubts. <br />
Answering the sales experts Q with a Q? Asking questions is lethal in interview situations. Sometimes good, but unless the question is brilliant and relevant, mostly something you should steer clear of. </p>

<p>And, telling the exec, that you &quot;hope to make a contribution as large&quot; is dangerous. It is unwise to put yourself in a comparative position vis a vis a &quot;great mans&quot; achievements. So, maybe better to just say that his work is inspirational, and legitimizes the company.</p>

<p>Keep on creating!</p>
